            <h3>Communication is Key</h3>
            <p>In Bandit mode, clear communication between teammates is essential. Use voice chat to coordinate:</p>
            <ul class="tips-list">
                <li><strong>Loadout Planning:</strong> Discuss your intended loadouts before the match starts.</li>
                <li><strong>Objective Coordination:</strong> Assign roles for objective control and defense.</li>
                <li><strong>Information Sharing:</strong> Relay intel from recon operators to the team.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Weapon Loadout Strategy</h3>
            <p>Consider your weapon choices carefully in Bandit mode:</p>
            <ul class="tips-list">
                <li><strong>M12:</strong> Excellent for mid-to-long range engagements. Great for operators who need versatility.</li>
                <li><strong>MP5:</strong> Perfect for close-quarters combat and entry fragging situations.</li>
                <li><strong>SMG Options:</strong> Consider SMGs like the MP7 or P90 for operators who will be pushing aggressively.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Grenade Usage</h3>
            <p>Strategic grenade usage can make or break a push:</p>
            <ul class="tips-list">
                <li><strong>Frag Grenades:</strong> Use for breaching walls and creating entry points.</li>
                <li><strong>Smoke Grenades:</strong> Essential for covering retreats, repositioning, and protecting operators with abilities.</li>
                <li><strong>Flashbangs:</strong> Critical for disorienting enemies during pushes or defending objectives.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

