            <h2>Defender Strategy in Bandit</h2>

            <h3>Area Control</h3>
            <p>As defenders, focus on controlling key areas and choke points:</p>
            <ul class="tips-list">
                <li><strong>Deploy Area Denial:</strong> Use operators like Mute or Kaid to control critical paths.</li>
                <li><strong>Objective Defense:</strong> Assign specific defenders to protect each objective area.</li>
                <li><strong>Information Gathering:</strong> Use recon operators to identify enemy positions before they push.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Counter-Breach Strategy</h3>
            <p>When facing breacher operators, consider these tactics:</p>
            <ul class="tips-list">
                <li><strong>Pre-plant Defenses:</strong> Set up defensive positions before the enemy breaches.</li>
                <li><strong>Use Area Denial:</strong> Deploy smoke and flash grenades to disrupt breaching attempts.</li>
                <li><strong>Coordinate Counter-Breach:</strong> Have a plan for when enemies breach - who covers, who pushes back.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Objective Control</h3>
            <p>Defenders should prioritize objective control:</p>
            <ul class="tips-list">
                <li><strong>Secure Objectives Early:</strong> Plant and defend objectives before the enemy can push.</li>
